ng, and to its eventual demise amid the moral panic over sexual behaviour during the 1950s and ‘60s.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCourtshipxHistoryx20th centuryxManitobaxWinnipeg Beach. 0aCourtshipzManitobazWinnipeg BeachxHistoryy20th century. 0aLeisurexHistoryx20th centuryxManitobaxWinnipeg Beach. 0aLeisurezManitobazWinnipeg BeachxHistoryy20th century. 0aResortsxHistoryx20th centuryxManitobaxWinnipeg Beach. 0aResortszManitobazWinnipeg BeachxHistoryy20th century. 0aTourismxSocial aspectsxManitobaxWinnipeg Beach. 0aTourismxSocial aspectszManitobazWinnipeg Beach. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088755403240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780887554032423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780887554032/original  a978-3-11-127414-0  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-127721-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010c2010d2011  aGBV-deGruyter-alles